<paragraph blockId="13.[264,1323,822,1649]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Remarks: This species is related to 
<taxonomicName box="[736,880,1503,1528]" class="Entognatha" family="Arrhopalitidae" genus="Arrhopalites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gnaspinii">
<emphasis box="[736,880,1503,1528]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">A. gnaspinii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and occurs in the same cave system but is found only in a single cave, it strinkingly differs from the closely related species in the group, by possessing two pairs of eyes and four ringed subsegments in Ant. IV (instead of six, as stated in original description). Id 
<number box="[765,776,1623,1649]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="1.0">1</number>
, Id 
<number box="[814,828,1623,1649]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="2.0">2</number>
and Id 
<number box="[909,923,1623,1649]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="4.0">4</number>
present on dens, L 
<number box="[1146,1160,1623,1649]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="4.0">4</number>
absent.
</paragraph>
